
// The code concatenates a URL by combining the scheme retrieved from a node, a static string "://", and the host from the request. It uses [strings.concat] to merge these elements into a single URL string. The [get-value] slot retrieves the scheme value, while [request.host] provides the host part of the URL.
strings.concat
   get-value:x:@.scheme
   .:"://"
   request.host
